### BlueForce API Tests
### Use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api
@token = your_jwt_token_here

### Authentication Endpoints

### Register New User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test123!",
  "role": "volunteer"
}

### Login User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Get Current User Info
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update User Profile
PUT {{baseUrl}}/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Name",
  "email": "updated@example.com"
}

### Change Password
PUT {{baseUrl}}/auth/change-password
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "password123",
  "newPassword": "NewPassword123!"
}

### Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get All Users (Admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get User Statistics (Admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Delete User (Admin only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/auth/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:4000/health

### Get All Events
GET {{baseUrl}}/events

### Get Events with Filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/events?upcoming=true
GET {{baseUrl}}/events?location=Marina
GET {{baseUrl}}/events?ngo_id=3

### Get Event Details
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/1

### Create New Event (NGO only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ngo_id": 3,
  "title": "Test Beach Cleanup",
  "description": "This is a test event for API testing",
  "location": "Test Beach, Test City",
  "date_time": "2024-03-15T09:00:00.000Z"
}

### Update Event (NGO owner or admin only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/events/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated Beach Cleanup Title",
  "description": "Updated description for the event"
}

### Delete Event (NGO owner or admin only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/events/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Enroll in Event (Volunteer)
POST {{baseUrl}}/events/1/enroll
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get Event Participants (NGO owner or admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/1/participants
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Cancel Enrollment
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/events/1/enroll
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get User Enrollments
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/users/1/events
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Mark Participation Complete (NGO only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/events/1/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": 1
}

### Get Event Statistics (NGO owner or admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/1/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get Events by NGO
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/ngo/3
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test Error Cases

### Create Event without Authentication
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ngo_id": 3,
  "title": "Unauthorized Event",
  "description": "This should fail",
  "location": "Test Location",
  "date_time": "2024-03-15T09:00:00.000Z"
}

### Create Event with Invalid Data
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ngo_id": 3,
  "title": "ab",
  "description": "This should fail validation",
  "location": "Test Location",
  "date_time": "2020-01-01T09:00:00.000Z"
}

### Get Non-existent Event
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/999

### Enroll in Non-existent Event
POST {{baseUrl}}/events/999/enroll
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
